  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Provision of lifesaving WASH assistance to South Sudanese refugees and host community in South Kordofan States</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="2">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The project aims at sustaining and expanding access to WASH services for 25,174 (4935 men 5135 women boys 7402 and 7702 girls under 18 years) South Sudanese refugees and host community in, Abu Gebeiha and Ellirri localities in South Kordofan State .Building on previous and current UNICEF WASH projects, the project will rehabilitate and upgrade the existing two water mini water yard and 13 hand pumps water supply systems to ensure the continuous operation of the system. It will also enable construction of one new water supply system and 150 shared household latrines and support hygiene promotion and water trucking for four months as an interim solution for water supply. The project will address significant gaps especially the reduction of WASH related diseases in new settlements and existing SSR camps.</narrative>
  </description>
